Governor Willie Obiano and other government officials welcomed the first set of passengers at the Anambra International Airport, in Umueri.  The passengers welcomed boarded the first Embraer 195-e2 aircraft at the airport. This is after approval was given by the Nigerian Civil Aviation Authority for the operation of Boeing 737-700 aircraft or its equivalent at the Anambra International Airport, in Umueri, The aircraft landed with 124 passengers from Lagos and the governor welcomed the passengers, including the pilot, with a handshake. The aircraft, from Air Peace Airline, one of the frontline carriers in Nigeria landed safely, from Lagos at Anambra International Cargo and Passenger Airport, Umueri. “This is a great day and that is why I came to welcome the first set of passengers that landed on this aircraft using a bigger plane,” he said.  Source Anambra State governor, Willie Obiano has stated that is the only Nigerian governor who does not receive a monthly salary. The governor explained that after his tax has been deducted from his salary, he sends the remaining balance to homes of destitute for their upkeep, adding that he has been… In "News" •Governor Willie Obiano, Governor of Anambra State Governor Willie Obiano’s direction of Anambra’s affairs will end on March 17, 2022. But his imprint on the state for eight straight years will endure. Not only endure, but also assume legendary proportions with the passage of time. Historians will wax lyrical on… In "Opinion" First aircraft have landed on the Anambra International Cargo and Passenger Airport in Umueri community, Anambra East Local Government Area of the state.  The aircraft are owned by Air Peace. A report in Daily Sun says the first one marked 5N-BUJ landed at exactly 2:25pm while the second one landed at about… In "Top Stories"